397 struct V8_EXPORT CachedData {
398 enum BufferPolicy { BufferNotOwned, BufferOwned };
399
400 CachedData()
401 : data(nullptr),
402 length(0),
403 rejected(false),
404 buffer_policy(BufferNotOwned) {}
405
406 // If buffer_policy is BufferNotOwned, the caller keeps the ownership of
407 // data and guarantees that it stays alive until the CachedData object is
408 // destroyed. If the policy is BufferOwned, the given data will be deleted
409 // (with delete[]) when the CachedData object is destroyed.
410 CachedData(const uint8_t* data, int length,
411 BufferPolicy buffer_policy = BufferNotOwned);
412 ~CachedData();
413
414 enum CompatibilityCheckResult {
415 // Don't change order/existing values of this enum since it keys into the
416 // `code_cache_reject_reason` histogram. Append-only!
417 kSuccess = 0,
418 kMagicNumberMismatch = 1,
419 kVersionMismatch = 2,
420 kSourceMismatch = 3,
421 kFlagsMismatch = 5,
422 kChecksumMismatch = 6,
423 kInvalidHeader = 7,
424 kLengthMismatch = 8,
425 kReadOnlySnapshotChecksumMismatch = 9,
426
427 // This should always point at the last real enum value.
428 kLast = kReadOnlySnapshotChecksumMismatch
429 };
430
431 // Check if the CachedData can be loaded in the given isolate.
432 CompatibilityCheckResult CompatibilityCheck(Isolate* isolate);
433
434 // TODO(marja): Async compilation; add constructors which take a callback
435 // which will be called when V8 no longer needs the data.
436 const uint8_t* data;
437 int length;
438 bool rejected;
439 BufferPolicy buffer_policy;
440
441 // Prevent copying.
442 CachedData(const CachedData&) = delete;
443 CachedData& operator=(const CachedData&) = delete;
444 };
445
446 enum class InMemoryCacheResult {
447 // V8 did not attempt to find this script in its in-memory cache.
448 kNotAttempted,
449
450 // V8 found a previously compiled copy of this script in its in-memory
451 // cache. Any data generated by a streaming compilation or background
452 // deserialization was abandoned.
453 kHit,
454
455 // V8 didn't have any previously compiled data for this script.
456 kMiss,
457
458 // V8 had some previously compiled data for an identical script, but the
459 // data was incomplete.
460 kPartial,
461 };
462
463 // Details about what happened during a compilation.
464 struct CompilationDetails {
465 InMemoryCacheResult in_memory_cache_result =
466 InMemoryCacheResult::kNotAttempted;
467
468 static constexpr int64_t kTimeNotMeasured = -1;
469 int64_t foreground_time_in_microseconds = kTimeNotMeasured;
470 int64_t background_time_in_microseconds = kTimeNotMeasured;
471 };

476 class Source {
477 public:
478 // Source takes ownership of both CachedData and CodeCacheConsumeTask.
479 // The caller *must* ensure that the cached data is from a trusted source.
480 V8_INLINE Source(Local<String> source_string, const ScriptOrigin& origin,
481 CachedData* cached_data = nullptr,
482 ConsumeCodeCacheTask* consume_cache_task = nullptr);
483 // Source takes ownership of both CachedData and CodeCacheConsumeTask.
484 V8_INLINE explicit Source(
485 Local<String> source_string, CachedData* cached_data = nullptr,
486 ConsumeCodeCacheTask* consume_cache_task = nullptr);
487 V8_INLINE Source(Local<String> source_string, const ScriptOrigin& origin,
488 CompileHintCallback callback, void* callback_data);
489 V8_INLINE ~Source() = default;
490
491 // Ownership of the CachedData or its buffers is *not* transferred to the
492 // caller. The CachedData object is alive as long as the Source object is
493 // alive.
494 V8_INLINE const CachedData* GetCachedData() const;
495
496 V8_INLINE const ScriptOriginOptions& GetResourceOptions() const;
497
498 V8_INLINE const CompilationDetails& GetCompilationDetails() const;
499
500 private:
501 friend class ScriptCompiler;
502
503 Local<String> source_string;
504
505 // Origin information
506 Local<Value> resource_name;
507 int resource_line_offset = -1;
508 int resource_column_offset = -1;
509 ScriptOriginOptions resource_options;
510 Local<Value> source_map_url;
511 Local<Data> host_defined_options;
512
513 // Cached data from previous compilation (if a kConsume*Cache flag is
514 // set), or hold newly generated cache data (kProduce*Cache flags) are
515 // set when calling a compile method.
516 std::unique_ptr<CachedData> cached_data;
517 std::unique_ptr<ConsumeCodeCacheTask> consume_cache_task;
518
519 // For requesting compile hints from the embedder.
520 CompileHintCallback compile_hint_callback = nullptr;
521 void* compile_hint_callback_data = nullptr;
522
523 // V8 writes this data and never reads it. It exists only to be informative
524 // to the embedder.
525 CompilationDetails compilation_details;
526 };
